data.title: Jane Child - Don't Wanna Fall In Love
data.meta_description: 'Don't Wanna Fall In Love' is taken from Jane Child's self-titled debut album, which droppped in 1989. Check out the long lost pop gem in The Guard's best song ever post.
data.text:
Woah there! Well how is this for a guilty pleasure?

“Don't Wanna Fall In Love” is taken from Jane Child's self-titled debut album, which droppped in 1989. And boy, did this synthtastic track cling on to what was left of the 80s for dear fucking life!

This song sat at #2 on the US chart for three weeks, kept from the top spot by Sinead O'Connor's ballad-that-was-actually-penned-by-Prince, “Nothing Compares 2 U.” Not that we are bitter or anything...

In all honesty, there is little else to tell you about Child, as she pretty much defines “one hit wonder.” She's probably working as a lunch lady nowadays or something like that. Oh, and living with her husband, totally contradicting the lyrical content of this song...

But most importantly - we wonder if she's still rocking her nose chain?

Lyrics:

Ain't no personal thing boy

but you have got to stay away

far, far away from my heart, my heart

don't you know what your kiss is doing

let me tell it to you from the start, boy

I don't wanna fall in love, no no

Love cuts just like a knife, woo woo

You make the knife feel good baby

I'll fight you to the end

You've been hanging around boy

And you have started sinking in

Whoa baby you're way out of line now

unaware how this all got started

let me tell it to you one more time boy

I don't wanna fall in love no no

love cuts just like a knife woo woo

you make the knife feel good baby

I'll fight you to the end

repeat

I learned something about myself

last night with you I knew

I didn't want nobody else

And your scaring me to death now baby

I don't wanna fall in love no no

love cuts just like a knife woo woo

you make the knife feel good baby

I'll fight you to the end

I don't wanna fall in love no no

Love cuts just like a knife woo woo

you make the knife feel good baby

I'll fight you to the end
